cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.DS, cs.CYBER, cs.MA 

This paper deals with social networks and their structural properties, which are typically studied in the field of social informatics (cs.SI) and social computing (cs.SOC). The paper also discusses sampling methods, which are relevant to data science (cs.DS) and cybernetics (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper proposes an estimator and uses Monte Carlo simulations, which are common in machine learning (cs.MA).
